# {{PROJECT_NAME}} Project Memory Guide

This file defines the durable memory contract for the repository.

The goal is simple:

- stable facts live in stable files
- current status lives in one place
- non-trivial decisions are written once and then linked
- releases and incidents keep their own operational history
- generated summaries never replace source documents

## Source Of Truth Layers

### Stable Project Facts

- `.sula/project.toml`
- `AGENTS.md`
- `docs/architecture/*`
- `docs/runbooks/*`

### Current State

- [{{STATUS_FILE}}](../{{STATUS_FILE}})

`{{STATUS_FILE}}` is the live handoff page. Its `## Handoff` section is the machine-checked transfer contract for the next device or operator.

### Decision And Delivery History

- [{{CHANGE_RECORDS_FILE}}](../{{CHANGE_RECORDS_FILE}})
- [{{CHANGE_RECORD_DIRECTORY}}/](../{{CHANGE_RECORD_DIRECTORY}})

### Release And Incident History

- [{{RELEASE_RECORD_DIRECTORY}}/](../{{RELEASE_RECORD_DIRECTORY}})
- [{{INCIDENT_RECORD_DIRECTORY}}/](../{{INCIDENT_RECORD_DIRECTORY}})

### Generated Recall Layer

- [{{MEMORY_DIGEST_FILE}}](../{{MEMORY_DIGEST_FILE}})

This digest is generated for fast recall. It is not a source of truth and should not be edited manually.

## Required Update Rules

1. Keep `{{STATUS_FILE}}` current after non-trivial work.
2. Record non-trivial changes in `{{CHANGE_RECORD_DIRECTORY}}/` and index them from `{{CHANGE_RECORDS_FILE}}`.
3. If a release has material rollout risk, add a release note.
4. If an incident affects availability, permissions, data, or deployment safety, add an incident record.
5. Every architecture exception should reference a change record.
6. If work touches `STATUS.md`, `CHANGE-RECORDS.md`, `docs/change-records/*`, `.sula/state/current.md`, `.sula/events/log.jsonl`, or `.sula/memory-digest.md`, finish by running `python3 scripts/sula.py check --project-root .` and require `SULA CHECK OK`.
7. `SULA CHECK OK` also requires `{{STATUS_FILE}}` to be at least as recent as the latest durable change, release, or incident record. A newer durable record without a status refresh is a hard failure.
8. `{{STATUS_FILE}}` must include a complete `## Handoff` contract with `ready: yes`, `start here`, `latest record`, a structured `next action`, `next owner`, `next due`, `done when`, `blockers`, `source of truth`, `source freshness`, structured verification fields, and explicit Git handoff state.
`next action` must include at least one actionable reference step and one runnable command step, for example:
`- next action: review \`docs/change-records/YYYY-MM-DD-topic.md\`; run \`python3 scripts/sula.py check --project-root .\``
`next due` must use `YYYY-MM-DD`, and `done when` should define the concrete handoff completion condition.
`done when` should be semi-structured and include at least one `result` or `artifact` step, for example:
`- done when: result \`SULA CHECK OK\`; artifact \`STATUS.md\``
Preferred standard `result` values include `SULA CHECK OK`, `doctor strict passed`, `sync dry run reviewed`, `record created`, and `handoff updated`. Custom results are still allowed, but Sula will surface an advisory so teams can standardize wording over time.
9. `## Recent Decisions` is a current-state panel, not a history log. Keep only the most recent `5` items; older decisions belong in change records.
10. If `Recent Decisions` overflows during automated updates, move the trimmed items into the status archive instead of dropping them.
11. `## Current Focus` and `## Blockers` are also capped current-state panels. If they outgrow the configured limit, archive or promote the overflow instead of stretching `{{STATUS_FILE}}`.

## Freshness Target

- `{{STATUS_FILE}}` should normally be updated at least every `{{STATUS_MAX_AGE_DAYS}}` days while the project is active.
- This freshness target is only an idle-project backstop. It does not replace the handoff rule above: after non-trivial work, `{{STATUS_FILE}}` still needs to catch up to the latest durable record before `check` can pass.

## Anti-patterns

- keeping key reasoning only in chat history
- mixing temporary task notes into stable architecture docs
- writing release reasoning into commit messages only
- editing the generated memory digest instead of the underlying records
- editing generated `.sula/*` state by hand when a Sula command can rebuild it
